-- Nigeria to sell three- and 10-year bonds in second quarter
-- By Oludare Mayowa
-- Mon Mar 31, 2014 07:09AM EDT
-- None



LAGOS, March 31 (Reuters) - Nigeria plans to auction a combined 75 billion naira ($454.5 mln) and 105 billion naira ($636.4 mln) of three-year and 10-year bonds during the second quarter, the country's debt management office said on Monday.

It will raise 25 billion naira in three-year bills and 35 billion naira in 10-year notes respectively in each of April, May and June.